headline: AP PHOTOS: Starlings, Indonesia's bicycle coffee sellers, peddle the streets of Jakarta
summary: Bicycles roam the streets of Indonesia's capital with dozens of plastic sachets of coffee and other packaged drinks dangling from their handlebars.  Tied in the back are large thermos bottles with hot water, an ice box and equipment for making coffee.  The bicycle coffee sellers are known as Starlings, an abbreviation of Starbucks Keliling, or mobile Starbucks, although they have no connection to the giant global coffee company.
